typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct CBOR.Value memory) pure returns (uint64[] memory)

returns._0: The `CBORValue.Error memory` decoded from the Result.

asErrorMessage(Witnet.Result).details: WARN: Note that client contracts should wrap this function into a try-catch foreseing potential errors generated in this function

returns._0: A tuple containing the `CBORValue.Error memory` decoded from the `Result`, plus a loggable error message.

asFixed16(Witnet.Result).details: Due to the lack of support for floating or fixed point arithmetic in the EVM, this method offsets all values. by 5 decimal orders so as to get a fixed precision of 5 decimal positions, which should be OK for most `fixed16`. use cases. In other words, the output of this method is 10,000 times the actual value, encoded into an `int32`.

returns._0: The `uint64[]` raw error as decoded from the `Result`.

params._cborBytes: Raw bytes representing a CBOR-encoded value.

params._stageIndex: A `uint64` identifying the index of one of the Witnet request stages.

returns._0: The name of the matching stage.

devdoc.title: A library for decoding Witnet request results

asBool(Witnet.Result).notice: Decode a boolean value from a Result as an `bool` value.

asBytes(Witnet.Result).notice: Decode a bytes value from a Result as a `bytes` value.

asErrorCode(Witnet.Result).notice: Decode an error code from a Result as a member of `ErrorCodes`.

asErrorMessage(Witnet.Result).notice: Generate a suitable error message for a member of `ErrorCodes` and its corresponding arguments.

asFixed16(Witnet.Result).notice: Decode a fixed16 (half-precision) numeric value from a Result as an `int32` value.

asFixed16Array(Witnet.Result).notice: Decode an array of fixed16 values from a Result as an `int128[]` value.

asInt128(Witnet.Result).notice: Decode a integer numeric value from a Result as an `int128` value.

asInt128Array(Witnet.Result).notice: Decode an array of integer numeric values from a Result as an `int128[]` value.

asRawError(Witnet.Result).notice: Decode a raw error from a `Result` as a `uint64[]`.

asString(Witnet.Result).notice: Decode a string value from a Result as a `string` value.

asStringArray(Witnet.Result).notice: Decode an array of string values from a Result as a `string[]` value.

asUint64(Witnet.Result).notice: Decode a natural numeric value from a Result as a `uint64` value.

asUint64Array(Witnet.Result).notice: Decode an array of natural numeric values from a Result as a `uint64[]` value.

isError(Witnet.Result).notice: Tell if a Result is errored.

isOk(Witnet.Result).notice: Tell if a Result is successful.

resultFromCborBytes(bytes).notice: Decode raw CBOR bytes into a Result instance.

resultFromCborValue(CBOR.Value).notice: Decode a CBOR value into a Result instance.

stageName(uint64).notice: Convert a stage index number into the name of the matching Witnet request stage.

userdoc.notice: The library exposes functions to check the Witnet request success. and retrieve Witnet results from CBOR values into solidity types.
